---
// Proof section — teaser only on the homepage.
// Full analysis lives at /analysis.
---

<section id="proof">
  <div class="container">

    <div class="section-head">
      <p class="section-label">The proof</p>
      <h2>One real object, read all the way through</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">
        The tool was run on a real object: a Mimbres Black-on-white bowl collected in 1923,
        held at the National Museum of Natural History. What follows is a sample of what
        it produced. Every claim is anchored.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="teaser">

      <!-- Excerpt -->
      <div class="excerpt">
        <p class="excerpt-label">From Pass 2 — artifact analysis</p>
        <div class="excerpt-text">
          <p>
            The slip and paint program routes this object through CHECK 1 of the tradition
            identification matrix: brilliant white to cream slip with a single dark pigment
            <span class="label label-obs">[OBS]</span>
            routes to CHECK 2 (Mimbres vs. Ancestral Puebloan disambiguation).
            <span class="label label-cons">[CONS]</span>
            CHECK 2 resolves immediately: the interior-dominant central medallion composition,
            angular stepped-diamond geometric program, single pigment, and coil-and-scrape
            construction all converge on Classic Mimbres Black-on-white.
            <span class="label label-cons">[CONS — Brody 2004, Shafer 2003]</span>
          </p>
          <p>
            The composition exhibits a designed positive-negative relationship: dark angular
            forms and white ground channels read interchangeably as figure and ground.
            <span class="label label-obs">[OBS]</span>
            This is a structural property of how the composition was built: a specific
            technical achievement Brody identifies as the core formal accomplishment of
            Mimbres geometric work, not a byproduct of black-on-white contrast alone.
            <span class="label label-interp">[INTERP — Brody; Mimbres geometric only]</span>
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Fingerprint sample -->
        <p class="fp-label">Sample — 6 of 29 perceptual principles</p>
        <div class="fp-sample">
          {[
            { code: 'ap_1',  name: 'Production Trace Reading',   score: 3 },
            { code: 'ap_8',  name: 'Symmetry as Evidence',        score: 3 },
            { code: 'ap_10', name: 'Color Zone Logic',            score: 3 },
            { code: 'ta_1',  name: 'Edge Detection',              score: 3 },
            { code: 'ta_4',  name: 'Figure-Ground Relationships', score: 3 },
            { code: 'ta_15', name: 'Closure / Negative Space',    score: 3 },
          ].map(p => (
            <div class="fp-row">
              <span class="fp-code">{p.code}</span>
              <div class="fp-bar-wrap"><div class="fp-bar fp-full"></div></div>
              <span class="fp-score">3</span>
              <span class="fp-name">{p.name}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
          <p class="fp-more">+ 23 more principles scored · full fingerprint in the analysis</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="teaser-cta">
        <div class="cta-meta">
          <p class="cta-object">Bowl A326247</p>
          <p class="cta-detail">Mimbres · NMNH Smithsonian · Accession 070367</p>
          <ul class="cta-what">
            <li>Complete Pass 1 blind observation</li>
            <li>Full Pass 2 analysis with epistemic labels throughout</li>
            <li>3 RAP Protocol flags with anchor counts</li>
            <li>All 29 principle scores with plain-English descriptions</li>
            <li>Pass 3 competency transfer</li>
            <li>Fingerprint vs. attribution comparison</li>
            <li>Provenance integrity assessment</li>
            <li>Documentation vs. observation contradiction check</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <a href="/corpus/2/analysis/2" class="read-analysis">Read the complete analysis →</a>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<style>
  section { background: var(--bg-alt); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .section-head { margin-bottom: var(--space-10); }
  .section-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-widest);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
    max-width: none;
  }
  h2 { font-size: clamp(var(--text-2xl), 3vw, var(--text-4xl)); letter-spacing: var(--tracking-snug); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .section-sub { font-size: var(--text-lg); color: var(--text-muted); line-height: var(--leading-body); }

  .teaser {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 300px;
    gap: var(--space-10);
    align-items: start;
  }

  /* Excerpt */
  .excerpt {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }
  .excerpt-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wider);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    max-width: none;
  }
  .excerpt-text { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-4); }
  .excerpt-text p { font-size: var(--text-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); max-width: 76ch; }

  /* Fingerprint sample */
  .fp-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    max-width: none;
  }
  .fp-sample { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-2); }
  .fp-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 44px 72px 20px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-3);
    align-items: center;
  }
  .fp-code { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--text-muted); }
  .fp-bar-wrap { height: 7px; background: var(--bg-alt); border-radius: var(--radius-xs); overflow: hidden; }
  .fp-bar.fp-full { width: 100%; height: 100%; background: var(--accent); border-radius: var(--radius-xs); }
  .fp-score { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); font-weight: var(--weight-bold); color: var(--accent); }
  .fp-name { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--text); }
  .fp-more {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    padding-top: var(--space-2);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    max-width: none;
  }

  /* CTA panel */
  .teaser-cta {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-6);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    position: sticky;
    top: calc(var(--space-16) + 60px);
  }
  .cta-object {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
    max-width: none;
  }
  .cta-detail { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .cta-what { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-2); }
  .cta-what li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    position: relative;
    line-height: var(--leading-snug);
  }
  .cta-what li::before { content: '—'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--border-strong); }
  .read-analysis {
    display: block;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: var(--white);
    text-align: center;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-6);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    transition: background var(--ease);
  }
  .read-analysis:hover { background: var(--accent-light); color: var(--white); }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .teaser { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .teaser-cta { position: static; }
  }
</style>
